<context>
	<score>0.4628822</score>
	<text>Kroni ( Tamil : ) is a figure in Ayyavazhi mythology . He is the primordial manifestation of evil , and manifests in various forms of evil, such as Ravana and Duryodhana , in different ages or yugas . In order to counteract and destroy the evil of Kroni&apos;s manifestations, Mayon (a Tamil name for Vishnu ), incarnates as avatars such as Rama and Krishna . He is analogous to Satan in the Judaeo-Christian tradition. He shares many similarities with the demon Kali of the Mahabharata and Kalki Purana .</text>
